        "Details": "A rarely seen alternative to the standard Warhammer that was released by Field Arms Systems Associates based on the plans for the standard Warhammer they obtained through industrial espionage. Only a few variants of this mech were produced before legal troubles forced the manufacturing to stop. Nevertheless it is just as effective a design as the standard Warhammer and shares many compatible spare parts, making it feasible to maintain for the forces that wound up purchasing it. The 6R variant was identical in layout to the standard Warhammer loadout of the same model designation, a fact that was instrumental in the lawsuit proving the espionage claims.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
